load ../infoflow-signature.maude

--- ============================ PRODUCER SIDE ============================

--- Coverage: a SOUND absent claim attests. i1 is declared absent and the internals
--- confirm noReach(i1); i2 is direct. The signature is justified, so it attests.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(abs(i1) dir(i2)) noReach(i1) reaches(i2)
  =>* C:Cfg attestsSig .

--- Coverage: a SOUND mediated claim attests. i1 flows only through c1, a cut, and c1
--- is not attacker steered; i2 is direct, so it attests.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) dir(i2)) mediated(i1,c1) nmifOk(c1) reaches(i2)
  =>* C:Cfg attestsSig .

--- Bite: UNDER-CLAIMED INDEPENDENCE. The signature declares i1 absent but the
--- internal check shows i1 actually reaches the result. The independence is unproven,
--- so it must never attest. RESIDUAL makes any attested state a solution, so No
--- solution proves the producer gate holds.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(abs(i1) dir(i2)) reaches(i1) reaches(i2)
  =>* attestsSig RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: BYPASSED MEDIATION. The signature claims i1 is mediated by c1, but some flow
--- path from i1 avoids c1. Mediation requires a cut, every path through c1; a bypass
--- leaks the i1 full label, so it must never attest.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) dir(i2)) bypasses(i1,c1) nmifOk(c1) reaches(i2)
  =>* attestsSig RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: ATTACKER-STEERED CROSSING, the NMIF guard. i1 is genuinely cut by c1, but
--- c1 selector is attacker influenced (nmifBad). A downgrade may not be attacker
--- steered (I-IFC3), so the mediated discount is unsound and never attests.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) dir(i2)) mediated(i1,c1) nmifBad(c1) reaches(i2)
  =>* attestsSig RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- ============================ CONSUMER SIDE ============================

--- Coverage end-to-end: a sound mediated signature whose GRANTED crossing caps i1 at
--- a public target, with i2 absent. The result is lo, so it is released.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) abs(i2)) mediated(i1,c1) nmifOk(c1) noReach(i2)
  clr(i1,hi) tgt(c1,lo) grant(c1)
  =>* C:Cfg accepted .

--- Bite, the FAIL-CLOSED CORE: UNGRANTED MEDIATED FALLS BACK TO DIRECT, NOT ABSENT.
--- Same attested signature and bindings as the coverage case, but the consumer does
--- NOT grant c1. If ungranted-mediated were wrongly treated as absent, i1 would
--- contribute nothing and the result would be lo and accepted. The correct semantics
--- falls back to direct: i1 contributes its full hi label, the result is hi, rejected.
--- No accepted state is reachable.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) abs(i2)) mediated(i1,c1) nmifOk(c1) noReach(i2)
  clr(i1,hi) tgt(c1,lo)
  =>* accepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: GRANTING IS NOT A BLANK CHECK. The consumer grants c1, but the c1 TARGET is
--- itself hi, the declassify ceiling is still secret for this audience. Even granted,
--- i1 contributes hi, the result is hi, rejected. A grant does not release past the
--- crossing own bounded target.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(med(i1,c1) abs(i2)) mediated(i1,c1) nmifOk(c1) noReach(i2)
  clr(i1,hi) tgt(c1,hi) grant(c1)
  =>* accepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: NO ATTESTATION, NO RELEASE. The signature is producer-unsound, absent over a
--- real flow, so it is never attested; even though the consumer bindings would fit a
--- lo result, the result can never be accepted. The producer gate guards the consumer.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-SIGNATURE :
  decl(abs(i1) abs(i2)) reaches(i1) noReach(i2)
  clr(i1,hi) clr(i2,hi)
  =>* accepted RESIDUAL:Cfg .
